news.title: Greentown China to issue $150 million additional bonds to refinance debt
news.para: The state-backed property developer last week said it sold $350 million worth of 8.45% senior notes due in 2028, the first dollar bond sale by a Chinese property developer since early 2023, in a sign that some investor appetite for speculative-grade China property debt could be returning.

news.title: Karnataka PWD minister directs officials to stop unauthorised construction on highways
news.para: Over the past two years, the district administration, in coordination with police department, identified black spots with high accident rates. Necessary scientific measures will be taken to prevent further accidents, with priority funding allocated for these projects.

news.title: Issue B-khata to properties in illegal layouts as one-time settlement: Karnataka CM
news.para: In residential areas in Karnataka, people get A-Khata for the layouts approved by the competent authorities such as Bengaluru Development Authority (BDA) or Urban Development Authorities.

news.title: Thailand's central bank considers measures to support property sector
news.para: Property developers have asked the central bank of Thailand to introduce polices, such as relaxing the loan-to-value rules that stipulate what percentage of a property's value can be given as a loans, Suwannee Jatsadasak told reporters.

news.title: German authorities give permission to 2.15 lakh buildings in 2024
news.para: German authorities gave the green light for just 215,900 buildings, 43,700 or 16.8% fewer than in the previous year, data from the German statistics office showed on Tuesday.

news.title: Tribeca Developers appoints Vaibhav Agarwal as executive director
news.para: Tribeca Developers is looking to raise institutional capital for upcoming projects and expand its development pipeline. It also is working towards an IPO.

news.title: Embassy Services promotes Saarang Ganapathi as CEO
news.para: With over 11 years of expertise in real estate management and seven years at ESPL, Saarang has previously held the position of chief operating officer (COO) in the company.

news.title: StarBigBloc Building Material acquires 57,500 sq meters land in Indore for Rs 6 crore
news.para: The company aims to expand its production capacity from current 250,000 cubic meters per annum to over 1.2 million cubic meters per annum in the next 4-5 years.

news.title: Amrita Singh buys Rs 18 crore apartment in Juhu
news.para: The apartment spans a built-up area of 252.04 sq meters (2,712.9 sq ft) and includes three car parking spaces.

news.title: Ranchi's VAMBAY housing complex in ruins, residents demand repairs
news.para: The Valmiki Ambedkar Awas Yojana housing complex in Chiroundi is in poor condition, with structural damages and unhygienic conditions affecting 864 families.

news.title: Germany's BASF sells Brazilian paint business to Sherwin-Williams for $1.5 billion
news.para: Sherwin-Williams, an American company, will acquire the unit, which has about 1,000 employees, said the world's largest chemicals group.

news.title: US President's tariffs are raising construction costs: Homebuilders
news.para: On Thursday, Trump announced sweeping plans for reciprocal tariffs that could upend global trade, and the home building industry is bracing for the impact.

news.title: Dubai developers score red-hot profits from global homebuyers
news.para: Dubai's property developers are experiencing soaring profits and record sales, driven by expats and overseas buyers. Emaar Development PJSC and Binghatti Holding Ltd. have seen earnings more than double.

news.title: Nimbus Projects reported pre-sales of Rs 491.37 crore in 9M FY25
news.para: Nimbus Projects' collections stood at Rs 183.38 crore in 9M FY25, reflecting year-on-year growth of 100.63% over Rs 91.03 crore collections registered in 9M FY24.

news.title: Delhi: Process kickstarted for repair of 2,400 flats for Savda Ghevra residents
news.para: These flats will be used to house slum dwellers currently residing in JJ bastis across different parts of the capital. The flats, built under the Jawaharlal Nehru National Urban Renewal Mission (JNNURM) nearly a decade ago, have been sparsely occupied, with only a few currently in use.

news.title: Hyderabad: Survey for Medchal & Shamirpet metro corridors speeds up
news.para: "We are conducting comprehensive traffic surveys to analyse current daily travel patterns and future projections. This includes studying junction movements, pedestrian footfall, and the percentage of commuters likely to switch to metro services," metro officials stated.

news.title: Economic self-reliance of urban bodies can give fillip to development: Madhya Pradesh CM
news.para: Explaining that the importance of urban bodies financial independence, the chief minister said, development can be given new momentum with economic self-reliance of urban bodies.

news.title: HC orders CBI probe into Rs 5,800 crore illegal sand mining in Tamil Nadu
news.para: A division bench comprising Justices S M Subramaniam and M Jothiraman directed the central agency to register criminal cases and launch investigation.

news.title: About 100 acres to be acquired for Visakhapatnam metro rail project
news.para: Of the total land, approximately 47 acres belong to the state govt, 36 acres belong to Vizag port, four acres to railways, three acres to central govt, and nine acres are privately owned.

news.title: Three illegal colonies razed on outskirts of Ludhiana
news.para: The exercise is part of the Greater Ludhiana Development Authority's (Glada)'s ongoing crackdown on unauthorised and unplanned development.
